BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 754.00 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 738.00 Tm (When traffic grows you have two options. Vertical scaling - scale up - means making a single) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 723.00 Tm (machine more powerful, more RAM and CPU. It's simple, but there's a hard ceiling - you can't add) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 708.00 Tm (RAM forever - and big machines get expensive. It's still one point of failure. Horizontal scaling -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 693.00 Tm (scale out - means adding more machines running the same service, behind a load balancer.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 678.00 Tm (There's no real ceiling, it's cost-effective with commodity hardware, and it's naturally fault-tolerant.) Tj ET
